properties.description: This place name Krožera derives from  Italian and Slovenian words for the crossroad (incroccio and križišče resprectively) and the Italian dialect word. It also the name of the olive oil mill in the house on the NW of the roundabout.

Please confirm this is a separate hamlet Križišče and not part of Srgaši.
See note. Do not know how to fix this.
properties.name: Krožera
properties.note: The village sign (signaling the start of the village) for Srgaši used to be on the SW part of the crossroad. The auhtorithies moved it to the main road towards NW of the roundabout so the village now includes the roundabout.
